overview: The user initiated a request to fix a pull request riddled with
  issues, including failing Vercel deploys. The process began by systematically
  addressing lint errors, critical security vulnerabilities like forgeable admin
  cookies (resolved by implementing HMAC-signed sessions with Web Crypto API for
  Edge Runtime), and various functional bugs such as incorrect PDF calculations
  and inert UI elements. A significant pivot occurred when a Next.js upgrade to
  version 16.1.1 was required to fix a critical security vulnerability
  (CVE-2025-66478), which subsequently introduced breaking changes in Prisma
  (v7) and ESLint. These dependency-related issues were resolved by updating
  Prisma schema configuration and adapting ESLint to the new flat config format.
  Ultimately, all code-related problems were fixed, and local builds passed. The
  persistent Vercel deployment failures were diagnosed as a platform-level
  configuration issue, specifically the absence of necessary environment
  variables like  in the Vercel project settings.
